(real README coming soon)

Usage: netgrowlnotify.py [options] [title]

Options:
  --version             show program's version number and exit
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -n NAME, --name=NAME  Set the name of the application that sends the
                        notification
  -s, --sticky          Make the notification sticky
  -m MESSAGE, --message=MESSAGE
                        Sets the message to be used instead of using
                        stdin
  -p PRIORITY, --priority=PRIORITY
                        Specify an int or named key (default is 0)
  -d IDENTIFIER, --identifier=IDENTIFIER
                        Specify a notification identifier (used for
                        coalescing)
  -H HOST, --host=HOST  Specify a hostname to which to send a remote
                        notification.
  -P PASSWORD, --password=PASSWORD
                        Password used for remote notifications.
  --port=PORT           Port number for UDP notifications.
  -t TITLE, --title=TITLE
                        Does nothing. Any text following will be treated
                        as the
  --prowl               Send notification to Prowl instead of Growl
  --prowl-key=PROWL_KEY
                        API key used for Prowl notifications
  --prowl-keyfile=PROWL_KEYFILE
                        Path to file containing Prowl API key
  --time-start=TIME_START
  --time-end=TIME_END   

